  Wait I know... I should go on welfare. Now THAT is a joke... right now if you're whole of body and mind, under 60, not pregnant, married, and don't have children it DOES NOT MATTER that you haven't eaten in a week. The available resources go to those in &quot;need&quot; first... regardless of how often you get dizzy and almost pass out at work because your daily diet consists of four slices of toast and enough water to make your stomach stop hurting.<br>
<br>
  Also, speaking english is considered AGAINST a person applying for any form of welfare.<br>
<br>
As to all the people who said it was spanish land first.... your point is what exactly? It's US land now.<br>
<br>
I don't recall reading in any history books that there were special rules for, say, german immegrants (damn, I just cannot seem to spell that today). ESL classes weren't in existance then... parents learned english, and taught it to thier children. They kept thier foods, thier religeon (sp?), thier clothing and music and celebrations... the only thing they &quot;lost&quot; was a language. <p><center><A HREF="http://www.clanautumnwood.com" TARGET="_top">
