CIA factbook. United States. Languages: English, Spanish (spoken by a sizable minority). The US does NOT have an official language. From 1849 to 1878, the Californian consititution required all official written material to be provided in both English <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and Spanish</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <p>----------------------------------<br>
